{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a3c15481-43f9-47e0-bbd3-7baa34c16d13","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch`**.\n\n- `dotnet watch test` will re-run tests automatically when you change source files.\n- `dotnet watch run` does the same for applications.\n\n`dotnet test` and `dotnet run` are one-shot commands; they don't monitor for file changes. The `watch` verb is what enables hot reload / live-reload behavior.\n\nSince your project appears to be a test project, you'd want:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e097d750-7386-41d2-b099-1914bafc3958","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to benefit from hot reload in a .NET project - specifically whether to use `dotnet test` or `dotnet run`. Let me look at their project to understand the context.","outputTokens":173,"requestId":"7C2E:175BE3:286B133:2CD88CB:69F94A68"},"id":"950ef017-8c43-4302-8c97-c3502eef7669","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:39:58.472Z","parentId":"0b81fc86-6711-4811-8500-8f90d6953587"}
